  "texts": [
    "In the struggle with nature and through production practice, human beings gradually accumulate experience and enhance understanding of fluid behavior.",
    "The continuous summarization and enhancement of these understandings gradually formed the discipline of fluid mechanics.",
    "The air and water we perceive in our daily lives appear to be continuous, and this perception is based on a macroscopic understanding of continuous flow.",
    "However, with the emergence of molecular kinetic theory, people gradually realized that the sense of continuity is because the distances between molecules are exceedingly small compared to the scales we typically perceive in our daily lives.In addition to the seemingly continuous flow of water and air, there exist various flows in our daily lives and industrial production that exhibit distinct discrete characteristics.",
    "Examples include dust explosions, particle flow, traffic flow, and the movement of crowds."
